-- KEY CONCEPTS EXPLAINED:
-- 1. BASE CASE: WHERE clause filters starting point
-- 2. RECURSIVE CASE: UNION ALL joins with previous result set
-- 3. Anchor Member: Initial SELECT before UNION ALL
-- 4. Recursive Member: SELECT after UNION ALL that references itself
-- 5. Termination: When no more rows match the JOIN condition
-- 6. MUST have termination condition to avoid infinite loops!
